PERSON 1 – GUI + Coordinator (Boss) - harini 

Responsibilities:

Connect GUI to backend (buttons → actions)

Load .tsp file from URL (NOT local file)

Parse coordinates into a list of cities

Split work into chunks (ex: 0–500, 500–1000, etc.)

Send tasks to workers through MQTT (using pub)

Receive results and pick the best path

Display final path, total distance, and time on GUI

Classes:

Main

Panel

ParseFile

Coordinator (boss logic that sends tasks & collects results)





PERSON 2 – Networking + Distributed System (MQTT) - Euclid 

Responsibilities:

Set up MQTT communication between machines

Implement publisher and subscriber

Handle sending tasks and receiving results

Implement outsourcer (controls worker execution on each machine)

Make sure ONLY URL + task info is sent (no file transfer)

Ensure all machines can connect and communicate properly

Classes:

Pub

Sub

Outsourcer (Runnable)

MQTTClientManager / message handler



PERSON 3 – Algorithm + Multithreading + Synchronization - Giselle


Responsibilities:

Implement Nearest Neighbor for Travelling Salesman Problem

Compute Euclidean distance between cities

Build worker threads to run computations in parallel

Use multithreading (ExecutorService or threads)

Implement synchronization (REQUIRED):

Producer–Consumer OR

Locks / Semaphores / Conditions

Create a thread-safe buffer (shared task queue)

Ensure no race conditions

Classes:

NearestNeighbors

Worker (Runnable)

Buffer (thread-safe queue)

Task / Result (data objects)